    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Action3<T1,T2,T3>, Action3Async<T1,T2,T3>, Event3<T1,T2,T3>, Event3AsyncDelegate<T1,T2,T3>, Event3Delegate<T1,T2,T3>

    public class Event3AsyncAdapter<T1,T2,T3>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Event3AsyncDelegate<T1,T2,T3>
    The Event3AsyncAdapter is class that adapts an Event3Delegate to Event3AsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously. All asynchronous event distributions are executed in another thread. The Executor to use for the asynchronous event distributions can be chosen during creation of this helper. If no explicit executor is given the a default executor is used. The default executor can be set using the AsyncExecutor.setDefaultExecutor(Executor) property or is created automatically by the AsyncExecutor.
    Author:
    tilmann
